## 3. File and Function Size Limits

Hard limits ‚ÄĒ refactor before exceeding:

| Item | Limit |
|------|-------|
| File length | **400 lines** (excluding docstrings/blank) |
| Function length | **50 lines** |
| Class length | **200 lines** |
| Function arguments | **5** (use a dataclass/TypedDict if more) |
| Cyclomatic complexity | **10** (Ruff `C901`) |
| Nesting depth | **4** |
| Module-level public symbols | **20** |

`app.py` currently exceeds the file limit ‚ÄĒ split into blueprints/services as it
changes. Any PR that touches an over-limit file must reduce its size.

